                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d273">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">384.11/124: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister Resident in Ethiopia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Addis Ababa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-05-03T10:00:00+02:35"
                            >May 3, 1936—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 3—6:02 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>269. My 268.<note n="21" xml:id="d273fn21">Not printed.</note> With cooperation
                    of British Legation which provided two trucks in charge of Vice Consul Trapman
                    the following were safely removed to British Legation this morning: Mrs. Bergman
                    and two children, Mr. and Mrs. Hansen, two Swedish and two Norwegian nurses. Dr.
                    Stadin will probably follow later. Dr. Bergman states he prefers to remain at
                    hospital.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
